use strict;
use warnings;

use Tirex;
use Tirex::Backend::Test;

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

my $backend = Tirex::Backend::Test->new($0);
$backend->main();

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------


__END__

=head1 NAME

tirex-renderd-test - Test renderer

=head1 SYNOPSIS

tirex-renderd-test

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This renderer creates a checkerboard test pattern for testing the Tirex
rendering system. It will be called from tirex-renderd-manager if you
configure it in /etc/tirex/renderer/test.conf.

tirex-renderd-test has no renderer specific configuration option. There
is one renderer specific configuration option for maps called "sleep".
It gives the time in seconds the renderer should sleep before notifying
the tirex-master to simulate a longer rendering time.

=head1 FILES

=over 4

=item F</etc/tirex/renderer/test.conf>

The configuration file.

=back

=head1 DIAGNOSTICS

Exits with exit code 1 if something went wrong.

=head1 AUTHORS

Frederik Ramm <frederik.ramm@geofabrik.de>, Jochen Topf
<jochen.topf@geofabrik.de> and possibly others.

=cut

